In [8]:
#Question 1.d
ranklist = [3, 10, 20, 30, 50, 60 ,70, 80, 100]
n=[]
error=[]
memory=[]
for i in (ranklist):
    reconstimg = np.matrix(u[:, :i]) * np.diag(s[:i]) * np.matrix(v[:i, :])
    entries = (2*i*512 + i) / (512*512)
    mse = np.square(np.subtract(imarray, reconstimg)).mean()
    #mse /= (512*512) for images, divide the error by size of the image. But it will not change the exhibition.
    title = "n = %s" % i ,"Error = %s" % mse, "Size to original data = %s"  %entries
    n.append(i)
    error.append(mse)
    memory.append(entries)
    print(title)

ranklist = [3, 10, 20, 30, 50, 60 ,70, 80, 100]
#ranklist = [3]
for i in (ranklist):
    reconstimg = np.matrix(u[:, :i]) * np.diag(s[:i]) * np.matrix(v[:i, :])
    plt.imshow(reconstimg, cmap='gray')
    entries = (2*i*512 + i) / (512*512)
    mse = np.square(np.subtract(imarray, reconstimg)).mean()
    title = "n = %s" % i , "Error = %s" % mse, "Relative memory usage = %s"  %entries
    plt.title(title)
    plt.show()

Question 1.f.

Rank 30 is acceptable, however rank 50 is quite similar to the original image while invading only 20%of the memory. Thus, rank 50 approximated SVD is enough for this specific image.
